cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and the evaluation of word vectors, which are commonly used in computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates how well word vectors encode perceptual and conceptual features, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of visual features, which could be related to computer vision and therefore cs.CV (Computer Vision) could also be a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of current word representations, which could be related to neural networks and therefore cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a possible category.
